The paper deals with optimizing the scheduling of transmission, reception, simultaneous reception and transmission, and silence in a wireless network, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of a full-duplex network, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions numerical simulations, which suggests that it may fall under machine learning (cs.MM) or machine learning applications (cs.LG).
